auditory, and

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:09,590
sometimes even all factory or
kinesthetic stimuli with it's own input.

4
00:00:09,590 --> 00:00:12,750
Augmented reality on the other hand,
compliments what you see and

5
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:14,190
hear in the real world.

6
00:00:14,190 --> 00:00:17,020
So for example, imagine a headset
like a Google Glass that

7
00:00:17,020 --> 00:00:20,220
automatically overlays directions
right on your visual field.

8
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,400
If you were driving,
it would highlight the route to take,

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,160
